{
  "texts": [
    "They introduce Execution Time Profiles (ETPs) to represent the relative frequencies of execution times for basic blocks and provide methods to combine these profiles to form an overall program profile.",
    "This approach involves using convolution operators and accounting for dependencies between basic blocks to create an accurate representation of the program's timing behavior.Kosmidis et al. [81] propose Path Upper Bounding (PUB) for time-randomized hardware, modifying programs to ensure uniform timing behavior across all paths.",
    "This method helps in retaining functionality while providing consistent timing information.",
    "In another work, Ziccardi et al. [82] introduce probabilistic padding to handle path coverage issues.",
    "This technique involves adding padding to account for path dependencies, ensuring comprehensive path coverage and improving the accuracy of the pWCET estimates."
  ]
}